{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-9163caa47af053a0","input":{"filename":"action_report.md","title":"Prioritized Action Report for On-call Runbook Executor","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report for On‑call Runbook Executor\n\n**Scope**: Review of current operational records for the On‑call Runbook Executor (agent 07‑oncall‑runbook‑executor) and recommendation of next actions.\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Assumptions\n- **Data source**: `analyze_records` (limit 10) returned three relevant records with risk/opportunity scores.\n- **Assumption**: Records reflect the most recent state of the queue and are representative of overall workload.\n- **No side‑effects** have been performed; all actions are read‑only diagnostics.\n\n---\n\n## Ranked Action Items (high → low priority)\n| Rank | Record ID | Title | Status | Impact | Risk Score | Opportunity Score | Recommended Action |\n|------|-----------|-------|--------|--------|------------|-------------------|--------------------|\n| 1 | **07‑A** | On‑call runbook executor priority case | urgent | 44,219 | **8** | 6.4 | Immediate execution: verify diagnostics steps, ensure handoff documentation is up‑to‑date, and notify the on‑call engineer for fast resolution. |\n| 2 | **07‑C** | On‑call runbook executor blocked follow‑up | blocked | 19,477 | **8** | 1.9 | Resolve cross‑functional blockers: coordinate with dependent teams, document required dependencies, and schedule a follow‑up meeting within 24 h. |\n| 3 | **07‑B** | On‑call runbook executor routine queue item | in_review | 9,791 | **2** | 1.0 | Continue standard review; schedule for routine handling after the higher‑priority items are cleared. |\n\n---\n\n## Action Plan\n1. **Address Record 07‑A** – As the highest‑impact and urgent item, allocate on‑call engineer time immediately. Verify that the runbook steps are followed, capture any anomalies, and update the handoff notes.\n2. **Unblock Record 07‑C** – Identify the exact dependency (e.g., external service, config change). Open a ticket with the responsible team, include the risk score, and set a deadline for removal of the block.\n3. **Process Record 07‑B** – Keep it in the review pipeline; no immediate escalation required.\n\n---\n\n## Next Steps\n- **Monitor** the status of 07‑A; confirm completion within the next shift.\n- **Escalate** any unexpected delay on 07‑C to the SRE lead.\n- **Document** any learnings from the execution of 07‑A to improve future runbook efficiency.\n\n---\n\n*Report generated automatically by the On‑call Runbook Executor agent (07‑oncall‑runbook‑executor).*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:06:48.479Z"}}
